msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Musāvādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 9"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "9. Duṭṭhullārocanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on telling about what is serious"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.31"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.9.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.219"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa295"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto chabbaggiyehi bhikkhūhi "
"saddhiṃ bhaṇḍanakato hoti."
msgstr ""
"At that time Venerable Upananda the Sakyan was quarreling with the monks "
"from the group of six."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.3"
msgid ""
"So sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitvā saṃghaṃ tassā āpattiyā "
"parivāsaṃ yāci."
msgstr ""
"At this time Upananda committed an offense of intentional emission of semen. "
"He then asked the Order for probation for that offense,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "Tassa saṃgho tassā āpattiyā parivāsaṃ adāsi."
msgstr "which he received."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.5"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyaṃ aññatarassa pūgassa saṃghabhattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "Just then an association in Sāvatthī was offering a meal to the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "So parivasanto bhattagge āsanapariyante nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Because Upananda was on probation, he was seated on the last seat in the "
"dining hall."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū te upāsake etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "The monks from the group of six then told those lay followers,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.8"
msgid ""
"“eso, āvuso, āyasmā upanando sakyaputto tumhākaṃ sambhāvito kulūpako; yeneva "
"hatthena saddhādeyyaṃ bhuñjati teneva hatthena upakkamitvā asuciṃ mocesi."
msgstr ""
"“Sirs, this Venerable Upananda, the esteemed associate of your families, "
"eats the food given in faith with the same hand he uses to emit semen."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.9"
msgid ""
"So sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitvā saṃghaṃ tassā āpattiyā "
"parivāsaṃ yāci."
msgstr ""
"After committing an offense of intentional emission of semen, he asked the "
"Order for probation for that offense,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "Tassa saṃgho tassā āpattiyā parivāsaṃ adāsi."
msgstr "which he received."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "So parivasanto āsanapariyante nisinno”ti."
msgstr ""
"And because he’s on probation, he’s seated on the last seat in the dining "
"hall.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa296"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.14"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhussa duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ "
"anupasampannassa ārocessantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six tell a person who’s not fully "
"ordained about a monk’s serious offense?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.15"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhussa duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ "
"anupasampannassa ārocethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.220"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.18"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhussa duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ "
"anupasampannassa ārocessatha."
msgstr ""
"Foolish men, how can you tell a person who’s not fully ordained about a monk’"
"s serious offense?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.20a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa297"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: bhikkhusammutiyā → bhik­khu­samma­tiyā (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.21"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhussa duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ anupasampannassa āroceyya, "
"aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk tells a person who is not fully ordained about another monk’s "
"serious offense, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "(<em>9</em>:<strong>58</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.9.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.9.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa298"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "… pe … ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa299"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "Bhikkhussāti"
msgstr "Another monk’s:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "aññassa bhikkhussa."
msgstr "a different monk’s."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa300"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "Duṭṭhullā nāma"
msgstr "A serious offense:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "āpatti—cattāri ca pārājikāni, terasa ca saṃghādisesā."
msgstr ""
"the four offenses entailing expulsion and the thirteen offenses entailing "
"suspension."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa301"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "Anupasampanno nāma"
msgstr "A person who is not fully ordained:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "bhikkhuñca bhikkhuniñca ṭhapetvā avaseso anupasampanno nāma."
msgstr "anyone except a fully ordained monk and a fully ordained nun."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa302"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid "Āroceyyāti"
msgstr "Tells:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "āroceyya itthiyā vā purisassa vā gahaṭṭhassa vā pabbajitassa vā."
msgstr "tells a woman or a man or a lay person or a monastic."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa303"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "Aññatra bhikkhusammutiyāti"
msgstr "Except if the monks have agreed:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "ṭhapetvā bhikkhusammutiṃ."
msgstr "unless he has the permission of the monks."

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.14a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.14b"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations part 1"

#. </h3><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.14c"
msgid ""
msgstr "Summary"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa304"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "Atthi bhikkhusammuti āpattipariyantā, na kulapariyantā."
msgstr ""
"There is permission of the monks with a limit on offenses, but not on "
"families."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.16"
msgid ""
"Atthi bhikkhusammuti kulapariyantā, na āpattipariyantā, atthi bhikkhusammuti "
"āpattipariyantā ca kulapariyantā ca, atthi bhikkhusammuti neva "
"āpattipariyantā na kulapariyantā."
msgstr ""
"There is permission of the monks with a limit on families, but not on "
"offenses. There is permission of the monks with a limit both on offenses and "
"on families. There is permission of the monks with a limit neither on "
"offenses nor on families."

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.16a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa305"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.17"
msgid "Āpattipariyantā nāma"
msgstr "With a limit on offenses:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.18"
msgid "āpattiyo pariggahitāyo honti—"
msgstr "offenses are specified:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.19"
msgid "“ettakāhi āpattīhi ārocetabbo”ti."
msgstr "“These particular offenses can be informed about.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa306"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.20"
msgid "Kulapariyantā nāma"
msgstr "With limit on families:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.21"
msgid "kulāni pariggahitāni honti—"
msgstr "families are specified:"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.221"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.22"
msgid "“ettakesu kulesu ārocetabbo”ti."
msgstr "“These particular families can be informed.”"

#. </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.23"
msgid "Āpattipariyantā ca kulapariyantā ca nāma"
msgstr "With a limit both on offenses and on families:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.24"
msgid "āpattiyo ca pariggahitāyo honti, kulāni ca pariggahitāni honti—"
msgstr "both offenses and families are specified:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.25"
msgid "“ettakāhi āpattīhi ettakesu kulesu ārocetabbo”ti."
msgstr ""
"“These particular offenses can be informed about, and these particular "
"families can be informed.”"

#. </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.26"
msgid "Neva āpattipariyantā na kulapariyantā nāma"
msgstr "With a limit neither on offenses nor on families:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.27"
msgid "āpattiyo ca apariggahitāyo honti, kulāni ca apariggahitāni honti—"
msgstr "neither offenses nor families are specified in this way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.28"
msgid "“ettakāhi āpattīhi ettakesu kulesu ārocetabbo”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </span></p><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.28a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Exposition"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa307"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.29"
msgid ""
"Āpattipariyante yā āpattiyo pariggahitāyo honti, tā āpattiyo ṭhapetvā aññāhi "
"āpattīhi āroceti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"When there is a limit on offenses, if he tells about other offenses than "
"those that are specified, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.32"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa308"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.30"
msgid ""
"Kulapariyante yāni kulāni pariggahitāni honti, tāni kulāni ṭhapetvā aññesu "
"kulesu āroceti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"When there is a limit on families, if he tells other families than those "
"that are specified, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa309"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.31"
msgid ""
"Āpattipariyante ca kulapariyante ca yā āpattiyo pariggahitāyo honti, tā "
"āpattiyo ṭhapetvā yāni kulāni pariggahitāni honti, tāni kulāni ṭhapetvā "
"aññāhi āpattīhi aññesu kulesu āroceti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"When there is a limit both on offenses and on families, if he tells about "
"other offenses than those that are specified and he tells other families "
"than those that are specified, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa310"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.1.32"
msgid "Neva āpattipariyante na kulapariyante, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"When there is a limit neither on offenses nor on families, there is no "
"offense."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations part 2"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.9.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa311"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid ""
"Duṭṭhullāya āpattiyā duṭṭhullāpattisaññī anupasampannassa āroceti, aññatra "
"bhikkhusammutiyā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If the offense is serious, and he perceives it as serious, and he tells a "
"person who is not fully ordained, then, except if the monks have agreed, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa312"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid ""
"Duṭṭhullāya āpattiyā vematiko anupasampannassa āroceti, aññatra "
"bhikkhusammutiyā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If the offense is serious, but he is unsure if it is, and he tells a person "
"who is not fully ordained, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits "
"an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa313"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid ""
"Duṭṭhullāya āpattiyā aduṭṭhullāpattisaññī anupasampannassa āroceti, aññatra "
"bhikkhusammutiyā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If the offense is serious, but he perceives it as not serious, and he tells "
"a person who is not fully ordained, then, except if the monks have agreed, "
"he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa314"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "Aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ āroceti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he tells about an offense that is not serious, he commits an offense of "
"wrong conduct."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa315"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.222"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid ""
"Anupasampannassa duṭṭhullaṃ vā aduṭṭhullaṃ vā ajjhācāraṃ āroceti, āpatti "
"dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he tells about the misconduct of a person who is not fully ordained, "
"whether serious or not, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa316"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "Aduṭṭhullāya āpattiyā duṭṭhullāpattisaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the offense is not serious, but he perceives it as serious, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa317"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid "Aduṭṭhullāya āpattiyā vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the offense is not serious, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense "
"of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa318"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.2.8"
msgid "Aduṭṭhullāya āpattiyā aduṭṭhullāpattisaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the offense is not serious, and he perceives it as not serious, there is "
"no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.9.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa319"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.3.2"
msgid "vatthuṃ āroceti no āpattiṃ,"
msgstr ""
"if he tells about the action which was the basis for the offense, but not "
"the class of offense;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.3.3"
msgid "āpattiṃ āroceti no vatthuṃ,"
msgstr ""
"if he tells about the class of offense, but not the action that was the "
"basis for the offense;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.3.4"
msgid "bhikkhusammutiyā,"
msgstr "if the monks have agreed;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.3.5"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.3.6"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa320"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc9:pts-cs2.3.7"
msgid "Duṭṭhullārocanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The ninth rule, the training rule on telling about what is serious, is "
"finished."

